node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: Ten years ago, there would have been no point to blind tasting a line-up of Jungle Bird variations: no bars were serving the cocktail, and no bartenders had a signature build. Today, the quasi-tiki cocktail is standard fare at almost any cocktail bar. Back in the day, we asked 10 of America's best bartenders to submit their finest recipe—and then blind-tasted them all to find the best of the best. See who took home top honors via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 22, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text:
Q: What do you get when you cross a White Negroni with a Gin Fizz? ⁠
⁠
A: @orlandofranklin’s White Negroni Fizz⁠
⁠
With the addition of soda water, a splash of lemon juice and a store-bought vegan foamer, McCray transforms the fairer Negroni into a tall frothy, well, fizz. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. ⁠
#drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 21, 2021. May be an image of food and drink.

node.text:
What is a frappé, anyway? While no one seems to be in agreement on what, exactly, defines them, some things are for sure: They’re cold, easy to make and delicious. Our five favorite tributes to the drink world’s frostiest mystery (like this pineapple-laced Amaretto Sour Frappé) via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch ⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 21, 2021. May be an image of food, drink and indoor.

node.text: In the Padua Paloma, @joshgoldman2 gives the Mexican highball an Italian accent, supplementing fresh grapefruit juice with bittersweet Aperol (an import from Padua, hence the drink’s name), while black sea salt garnishes the rim. Topped with sparkling water in place of Squirt, the drink is a craveable Paloma-spritz mashup. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @dylanandjeni

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 20, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Joaquín Simó describes the Naked & Famous as “the bastard child born out of an illicit Oaxacan love affair between the classic Last Word and the Paper Plane.” Sticking to equal parts, the mezcal-Aperol-Chartreuse-lime combo has made the jump that every modern classic riff aspires to—becoming a bona fide modern classic itself. Get the recipe, plus five other remixed modern classics, via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 20, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text:
Born at Camparino in Galleria, a bar opened in 1915 by Davide Campari—son of the formula’s creator, Gaspare Campari—the Campari & Soda (@campariusa #punchpartner) has been an ambassador for Milanese drinking culture ever since. And, as Americans have come to embrace all things bitter and bubbly, the combo appears to finally be coming into its own stateside. Head to the link in our profile to take a dive into the art, culture and countless memorable moments inspired by the iconic duo and find out why, over a hundred years since its invention, the Campari & Soda has never been more relevant. ⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 19, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: A modern take on the Peachtree Punch, Martin Cate rejiggered the 1970s Trader Vic recipe one ingredient at a time. Fresh peaches and housemade coconut cream replace their canned alternatives, while natural peach liqueur stands in for schnapps and lemon juice is added for an extra jolt of acidity. Check out the full recipe for his remake of the classic tiki drink via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @aubrieprick

Margaritas get all the attention, but @joshgoldman2 prefers to celebrate another agave all-star: the Paloma. “It’s such a great framework for a cocktail,” he says. “The flavors go with just about anything. It’s bulletproof.” Over the years, he’s created multiple versions of the sweet-tart classic, a highball typically made with tequila, grapefruit soda and a squeeze of lime. His classic version, which took a top spot in a PUNCH blind tasting, tops tequila and fresh lime with Squirt, a wedge of grapefruit and a pinch of salt, but his roster of nontraditional versions shows just how versatile the Paloma blueprint can be. node.text: In 2006, few people in the United States understood the appeal of gin or pastis. @audreysaunders’ rather counterintuitive solution to this problem was to put both the gin and the pastis in the same shaken drink—along with lime juice, simple syrup and mint leaves. She called it the French Pearl. In recent years, the unusual cocktail has developed a reputation as a kind of unsung classic, a @peguclub_nyc staple that got somewhat buried and lost under all the praise heaped on better-known Saunders drinks like the Old Cuban, Gin-Gin Mule and Little Italy. Head to the link in our profile where @robertosimonson cements its status as a modern classic. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro
